&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 1&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47939702</guid><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 19:53:10 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Why don't AI coding tools like REST?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47939342</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Is it just me, or do AI coding tools tend to generate RPC-style endpoints and POST methods (even when GET is clearly all that is needed) instead of following RESTful conventions?&lt;p&gt;Given how advanced these models are, I'm wondering if this is intentional. Is AI saying it has determined that strict REST isn’t a practical standard all around? Or is it just a byproduct of token efficiency or....?&lt;p&gt;I know I can steer the output with better prompting, but I'm curious whether there's a real underlying reason for this almost all-the-time output.&lt;/p&gt;
